  "prompt": "What programming languages are used at Quora ?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Quora primarily uses a combination of programming languages in its tech stack. The main languages include:\n\n1. **Python**: Quora's backend is largely built using Python, which is favored for its ease of use and the rich ecosystem of libraries and frameworks available.\n\n2. **JavaScript**: For front-end development, Quora employs JavaScript, along with frameworks and libraries like React, to build interactive user interfaces.\n\n3. **Java**: While less prominent than Python, Java may still be used for certain backend services or infrastructure components.\n\n4. **C++**: Quora has employed C++ for performance-critical parts of its system.\n\n5. **SQL**: For database management and queries, SQL is used to handle and manipulate structured data.\n\nAdditionally, Quora utilizes various other tools and technologies for infrastructure, deployment, and data handling. The exact technology stack can evolve over time, so for the latest information, it's a good idea to refer to Quora's tech blogs or their engineering section.",
